          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " This double-sided Cf-252 source produced in Radium",
                " Institute, St Petersburg, by self-transfer method",
                " onto 22 microg/cm*82 aluminum oxide support backing",
                " with a 10 microg/cm**2 layer of gold.",
                " Activity of 500 fis/sec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   Particle separation based on the E vs TOF",
                "        analysis."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence of LCP and both FFs."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "SI",
                "PLATE",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "- 10 unshielded silicon p-i-n diode detectors",
                " (380 microg thickness, 30x30 mm**2 area) for LCP",
                "detection. Placed at 20 cm from Cf-source.",
                "- Micro channel plate detector (MCP) at 2.5 cm distance",
                "from Cf-source. For FF registration to give start",
                "signal.",
                "- 2 silicon p-i-n diodes of 20x20 mm**2 area (roof",
                "detectors) at 6 cm distance from Cf-source, opposite",
                "MCP. For coincident registration of complementary",
                "fragments.",
                " Energy threshold  =< 0.5 MeV.",
                " At high energy the ternary alpha-particle spectrum is",
                " cut off at 27.5 MeV due to the limited detector",
                " thickness of 380 microm; for H-3 particles - 11.5 MeV.",
                " Energy calibration of silicon detectors was performed",
                " with alpha-lines from spectroscopic thin Ra-226 source",
                " and BNC PB5 precision pulse generator, to better than",
                " 50 keV (FWHM).",
                "Nominal thickness of aluminum layer on entrance of",
                "silicon detectors 140 nm.",
                "Detector geometry registered alpha-particles with angle",
                "between ternary particle and LF from 55 deg to 13 deg.",
                "Efficiency function has FWHM of 33 deg around 92 deg",
                "mean angle."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " For energy loss - 110 keV for 1 MeV alpha-particles,",
                " 30 keV for 10 MeV alpha-particles.",
                " Measured TOF spectra of ternary particles were",
                " corrected for",
                " - the difference in flight time between heavy and",
                " light fragment masses from source to MCP;",
                " - the wider than detected angular interval of",
                " equatorial particles, best defined as in range",
                "50 - 130 deg according to P.Heeg data;",
                "- full span of angles, including polar emission, as",
                "measured in REL-REFs of C.Wagemans+, Yu.Kopatch+,",
                "V.Tishchenko+ ."
              ]
            }
          ],
